text: Urogonodes macrura is a moth in the family Drepanidae. It was described by Warren in 1923. It is found in New Guinea, where it is probably restricted to higher mountains. It is a variable species.The Hooktips (Drepanidae, Drepaninae) of Papua Indonesia ==References== Category:Moths described in 1923 Category:Drepaninae
title: Urogonodes macrura
